        <abstract> 
<p>JBJ explains his theory of atmospheric denudation of Irish river valleys, to be published [as "On the river valleys in the south of Ireland", <hi rend="italic">Q. J. Geol. Soc. Lond.</hi> 18 (1862): 378–403], and suggests its application to the Weald. This slow process would make the Weald far older than CD’s 300 million years.</p>  
<p>Thanks for <hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
